WEBVTT

00:00.957 --> 00:03.481
He's not the child that
we envisioned, but he's ours.

00:03.612 --> 00:04.613
[Rebecca] I take it you put
Rose Mallory's

00:04.743 --> 00:07.311
accusation to rest?

00:07.442 --> 00:09.661
[Charles] I believe
my cousin Stephen is alive.

00:09.792 --> 00:13.535
I was lured here under
the pretense of an inheritance.

00:13.665 --> 00:15.798
-To what end?
-I wouldn't know.

00:15.928 --> 00:17.800
-Where are my shells?
-[Tane] I didn't take 'em!

00:17.930 --> 00:19.410
[Honor]
You found your necklace.

00:19.541 --> 00:21.717
-[gasps]
-[Frost] Is it the worms?

00:21.847 --> 00:24.285
You see them, don't you?

00:24.415 --> 00:27.244
Silence, Stephen,
and Phillip

00:27.375 --> 00:29.507
were all driven mad by them.

00:29.638 --> 00:30.639
I'm not mad.

00:34.643 --> 00:35.731
[Frost] It's hereditary.

00:35.861 --> 00:38.212
Blood calls blood, son.

00:38.342 --> 00:39.430
[Robert grunts]

00:39.561 --> 00:41.476
A strange girl
gave me an apple.

00:41.606 --> 00:43.521
Tell your father
to find the book!

00:44.827 --> 00:46.220
-[Tane] There were worms in it.
-[Tane screams]

00:46.350 --> 00:47.395
You saw them?

00:47.525 --> 00:48.570
I did.

00:49.745 --> 00:50.789
I'd better go.

00:52.313 --> 00:53.531
[rattling]

00:53.662 --> 00:54.750
There are no rats!

00:54.880 --> 00:56.099
There are no rats!

00:57.318 --> 00:59.842
[grunts]

00:59.972 --> 01:00.669
-[Charles grunts]
-[Loa screams]

01:00.799 --> 01:01.626
Charles, no!

01:01.757 --> 01:03.324
♪♪♪

01:11.767 --> 01:15.205
[soft violin music]

01:54.418 --> 01:56.768
[distorted violin]

02:14.786 --> 02:15.613
[violin music stops]

02:15.744 --> 02:16.658
[boy, muffled] Mother?

02:18.529 --> 02:19.443
Mother?

02:21.924 --> 02:22.968
[clearly] Mother!

02:23.099 --> 02:25.754
-Yes, Phillip.
-Is that enough?

02:25.884 --> 02:27.321
Can Robert and I
go outside now?

02:28.539 --> 02:29.801
All right.

02:39.028 --> 02:44.425
♪♪♪

02:46.949 --> 02:50.213
[theme music plays]

04:17.953 --> 04:19.259
[Honor] Father?

04:22.914 --> 04:24.568
-Father.
-[both gasp]

04:24.699 --> 04:28.572
[breathing heavily]

04:32.010 --> 04:33.882
What time is it?

04:34.012 --> 04:35.579
Midday.

04:43.718 --> 04:44.675
Are you feeling okay?

04:46.198 --> 04:47.809
I've never seen you
sleep for so long.

04:52.074 --> 04:53.467
Tired, is all.

04:56.557 --> 04:57.819
Here.

04:57.949 --> 04:59.342
You should eat something.

05:03.694 --> 05:04.478
[sighs]

05:06.044 --> 05:08.525
Where's
your brother and sister?

05:08.656 --> 05:09.570
Doing lessons
with Miss Morgan.

05:11.180 --> 05:12.616
Loa's still upset.

05:17.926 --> 05:18.927
Honor.

05:20.798 --> 05:21.756
Come.

05:29.111 --> 05:30.460
Last night...

05:37.162 --> 05:39.077
My behavior was indefensible.

05:43.212 --> 05:44.735
You don't have to explain
yourself to me.

05:48.957 --> 05:50.872
[sighs] Rest.

05:57.139 --> 05:58.488
[door closes]

06:00.838 --> 06:02.884
[birds chirping]

06:06.322 --> 06:07.367
[woman] Faith.

06:11.936 --> 06:12.937
Who's there?

06:14.765 --> 06:17.551
♪♪♪

06:20.858 --> 06:21.859
[woman] Faith...

06:27.125 --> 06:27.996
Faith.

06:29.780 --> 06:30.781
Now look what
you've gone and done.

06:36.265 --> 06:38.833
-Don't come any closer!
-Faith.

06:38.963 --> 06:41.575
Is that any way
to treat an old friend?

06:44.186 --> 06:46.101
I'm not goin' back.

06:46.231 --> 06:47.842
Oh, sweetheart.

06:53.717 --> 06:55.415
You never left.

06:56.720 --> 06:57.939
You gave your blood.

07:03.118 --> 07:05.076
Just like the rest of us.

07:08.384 --> 07:09.559
You made a promise.

07:12.780 --> 07:14.695
Always is always.

07:15.913 --> 07:17.698
Forever, Faith.

07:25.227 --> 07:27.055
I haven't said anything.

07:27.185 --> 07:29.144
-I won't.
-We know.

07:31.320 --> 07:33.104
But where do you think
you're running to?

07:33.235 --> 07:37.108
His reach is infinite.

07:37.239 --> 07:39.850
No one can hide
from the worm, child.

07:42.331 --> 07:45.856
You can still be reborn,Faith.

07:45.987 --> 07:48.293
Bring the minister...
and your baby.

07:48.424 --> 07:50.861
He won't mind.

07:50.992 --> 07:53.168
Remember,
Jakub never loses a lamb.

08:25.113 --> 08:25.896
[knocking on door]

08:28.986 --> 08:31.511
-Enter.
-[door creaks]

08:35.906 --> 08:37.995
Happy to see
you're doing better.

08:38.126 --> 08:41.346
I am. Thank you.

08:41.477 --> 08:44.045
Charles, may I be frank?

08:44.175 --> 08:45.655
Yes, of course.

08:46.743 --> 08:48.919
Are the children and I
in danger...

08:49.050 --> 08:50.834
from you?

09:07.503 --> 09:09.200
I can't answer that.

09:19.820 --> 09:21.822
Sit, please.

09:36.314 --> 09:39.274
When I was a boy,

09:39.404 --> 09:41.276
my father tried to kill me.

09:46.368 --> 09:47.978
I remember...

09:50.459 --> 09:53.157
kneeling above
the shallow grave

09:53.288 --> 09:54.637
he had dug for me...

09:57.597 --> 09:59.207
...waiting for the final blow.

10:01.296 --> 10:02.645
It looked like him.

10:04.212 --> 10:07.041
Moved, sounded like him,

10:07.171 --> 10:09.739
but no sign of the man
I loved remained.

10:12.002 --> 10:14.091
I will not have that
for my children.

10:14.222 --> 10:17.138
So you believe you're
becoming like your father?

10:17.268 --> 10:20.315
When I spoke with Dr. Frost
yesterday,

10:20.445 --> 10:23.187
he confirmed my worst fears.

10:37.245 --> 10:38.638
I see things.

10:40.291 --> 10:41.902
Things that aren't real.

10:43.338 --> 10:45.775
Things my father spoke of.

10:47.995 --> 10:49.953
I have for some time now.

10:52.913 --> 10:54.915
Charles...

10:55.045 --> 10:57.482
Even if I...

10:57.613 --> 10:58.962
never hurt my children,

10:59.093 --> 11:01.443
I'm terrified that one day
they will suffer

11:01.573 --> 11:05.099
from the same affliction
that tortures me.

11:08.058 --> 11:11.671
S-s-so, what do you
intend to do?

11:11.801 --> 11:14.151
I'm going to see Dr. Frost
this morning.

11:14.282 --> 11:17.111
Charles...

11:17.241 --> 11:18.852
people don't return
from Frigate Island.

11:21.245 --> 11:23.465
I need help.

11:23.595 --> 11:25.249
I don't trust myself.

11:30.907 --> 11:33.388
I'm so sorry. I...

11:33.518 --> 11:36.173
I never intended to burden you
with any of this. I...

11:38.262 --> 11:40.003
Besides my wife...

11:42.527 --> 11:45.182
I've never spoken of
my situation with anyone.

11:47.184 --> 11:49.317
I trust you'll do the same.

11:52.363 --> 11:54.235
Father!

11:54.365 --> 11:55.105
Tane found
something in the barn!

11:58.500 --> 12:00.850
♪♪♪

12:15.735 --> 12:17.084
[Tane] I was going
to go down there,

12:17.214 --> 12:18.738
but I thought
I heard someone.

12:24.134 --> 12:25.745
What do you think
is down there?

12:30.532 --> 12:32.012
I'm going to find out.

12:35.798 --> 12:37.974
Tane, go inside
with Miss Morgan.

12:38.105 --> 12:40.324
-But I found it!
-Inside.

12:40.455 --> 12:42.152
Come on. We still have
a lesson to finish.

12:43.588 --> 12:45.895
Honor, light a lamp.

12:52.467 --> 12:55.209
♪♪♪

12:55.339 --> 12:57.385
[Charles grunts]

13:04.218 --> 13:06.089
I don't think it's safe
to go down there.

13:08.091 --> 13:09.484
Hand me the lamp.

13:31.506 --> 13:34.117
[distorted soundscape]

13:58.576 --> 14:02.015
[grunts]

14:29.303 --> 14:30.347
[straining]

14:37.615 --> 14:39.182
[softly] You son of a bitch.

15:04.381 --> 15:07.341
[eerie soundscape]

16:04.267 --> 16:11.666
[dissonant violin music]

17:07.722 --> 17:11.030
[woman's voice, muffled]

17:19.342 --> 17:21.170
[muffled voice]

17:21.301 --> 17:22.302
Rebecca?

17:24.652 --> 17:25.696
[Rebecca] Charles?

17:30.005 --> 17:31.833
Charles? Is that you?

17:31.963 --> 17:33.704
[Charles]
The tunnel leads to the house.

17:33.835 --> 17:36.533
There are passageways
inside the walls.

17:36.664 --> 17:39.275
There's a room back here
that's been walled off.

17:39.406 --> 17:41.060
An entire room?

17:42.235 --> 17:43.323
Yes.

17:48.893 --> 17:51.200
[softly] I found you,
you son of a bitch.

17:56.075 --> 17:59.078
Don't stop for anyone or
anything until you reach Able.

17:59.208 --> 18:01.471
Tell him to ride like
the wind and bring his rifle.

18:01.602 --> 18:02.820
All right.

18:04.083 --> 18:07.129
Stephen played me for a fool,
and put my family in peril.

18:09.914 --> 18:12.395
I need to hunt him down
before he hurts anyone else.

18:24.059 --> 18:26.757
[birds chirping]

18:32.372 --> 18:33.416
Faith.

18:37.768 --> 18:40.945
-My love.
-Martin.

18:41.076 --> 18:42.991
We have to leave.

18:43.122 --> 18:44.601
Have you bought the tickets?

18:44.732 --> 18:46.864
-Soon.
-No!

18:48.301 --> 18:51.086
There are a few things that
I have to do before we leave.

18:51.217 --> 18:54.916
We don't have time.
We need to leave now.

18:55.046 --> 18:56.744
And we will.
It's more complicated

18:56.874 --> 18:58.354
than you can understand.

18:58.485 --> 19:00.574
If we stay,
we're going to die.

19:06.493 --> 19:08.669
Those people who harmed you,

19:08.799 --> 19:09.713
they don't know
where you are.

19:09.844 --> 19:11.759
You're wrong!

19:11.889 --> 19:13.500
One of them came to me today.

19:13.630 --> 19:14.762
They know where I am.

19:15.980 --> 19:17.634
They know about you,

19:17.765 --> 19:19.288
and our baby.

19:19.419 --> 19:20.289
What?

19:21.899 --> 19:22.944
Who came to you?

19:23.074 --> 19:26.382
I... I don't know her name.

19:26.513 --> 19:27.688
Not her real name.

19:30.995 --> 19:33.563
These people are evil.

19:35.043 --> 19:37.176
They're unlike you or me.

19:38.873 --> 19:40.179
Please, Martin.

19:42.137 --> 19:43.225
Bad things are coming.

19:46.141 --> 19:47.316
[Martin sighs]

19:56.630 --> 19:58.675
If you're not gonna leave
your wife, tell me.

20:01.635 --> 20:03.854
Tell me so I can take
our child and go.

20:05.421 --> 20:07.641
[bell dinging]

20:07.771 --> 20:09.817
We will leave.

20:09.947 --> 20:11.340
I'll get the tickets.

20:14.735 --> 20:15.823
I will.

20:27.965 --> 20:30.272
[door closes]

20:35.016 --> 20:37.366
[Mary breathing unsteadily]

20:50.205 --> 20:52.686
[breathing unsteadily]

21:05.786 --> 21:06.743
[footsteps approaching]

21:11.748 --> 21:12.662
Mary?

21:17.798 --> 21:19.582
What are you doing
out of bed?

21:28.243 --> 21:29.592
It's so cold.

21:30.985 --> 21:32.291
[liquid dripping on floor]

21:37.557 --> 21:44.433
♪♪♪

21:44.564 --> 21:46.870
[Martin] Dear Lord,

21:47.001 --> 21:50.613
we commit
Thine blessed child,

21:50.744 --> 21:54.269
Susan Mallory, taken from us
too soon, to the earth.

21:54.400 --> 21:58.012
And we ask that
You fill our hearts

21:58.142 --> 22:00.493
with forgiveness and love,

22:00.623 --> 22:01.624
in place of hate.

22:03.757 --> 22:07.413
That you heal us
with understanding

22:07.543 --> 22:09.763
instead of anger.

22:09.893 --> 22:13.332
That you grace us
with righteous truth

22:13.462 --> 22:16.987
and deliver us from the devil's
poisonous salve of idle gossip.

22:19.207 --> 22:20.991
Let us not become the beast

22:21.122 --> 22:23.559
that feeds on sorrow
and vengeance,

22:23.690 --> 22:25.866
heedless and heartless.

22:25.996 --> 22:27.868
Let us instead
become the light

22:27.998 --> 22:30.827
that can guide others through
this ever-present darkness

22:30.958 --> 22:32.742
that seeks to consume us
in these trying times.

22:37.356 --> 22:40.533
My child lies in dirt, while
my husband remains missing!

22:40.663 --> 22:42.404
Rose, we've searched.

22:42.535 --> 22:44.101
Why aren't you turning over
every inch of Chapelwaite

22:44.232 --> 22:46.190
looking for him?Rose, please.

22:46.321 --> 22:48.192
It's the Boones that did this!
She named her killer!

22:48.323 --> 22:49.759
I know you're upset--

22:51.805 --> 22:53.937
Why are you not hunting
Stephen Boone!?

22:55.156 --> 22:57.027
Because he's dead, Rose.

22:59.726 --> 23:03.033
Better you leave,
Constable,

23:03.164 --> 23:05.688
before I earn
a stay in your cell.

23:10.998 --> 23:13.043
I'm sorry for your loss.

23:30.104 --> 23:31.584
[Able] Mr. Boone?

23:33.281 --> 23:35.196
Able.
Thank you for coming.

23:35.326 --> 23:36.937
Yes, sir.

23:37.067 --> 23:38.808
Is it Thompson
and his friends again?

23:38.939 --> 23:40.593
Worse.

23:40.723 --> 23:43.117
We have a stowaway.

23:43.247 --> 23:45.075
My cousin Stephen

23:45.206 --> 23:47.600
is living inside
the walls of this house.

23:50.080 --> 23:52.996
I'm gonna capture him
before he can do any more harm.

23:55.564 --> 23:57.740
-It's true.
-[Charles] It's almost dark.

24:00.439 --> 24:02.005
That's when he returns.

24:02.136 --> 24:05.574
I'll need you both
to protect Loa and Tane.

24:05.705 --> 24:07.446
Yes, sir.

24:29.946 --> 24:30.947
[Charles] Close it.

24:35.865 --> 24:38.912
♪♪♪

25:52.028 --> 25:53.116
[grunts]

26:02.256 --> 26:04.824
[crows cawing]

26:18.359 --> 26:20.013
I couldn't find you
at the reception.

26:22.319 --> 26:27.237
I'm-I'm not feeling
quite... altogether.

26:30.327 --> 26:32.939
It's over now.

26:33.069 --> 26:34.593
Rose Mallory left early.

26:37.073 --> 26:38.597
I know how she feels.

26:40.599 --> 26:44.820
Who can stand small talk
and endless consolation

26:44.951 --> 26:48.345
when your child lies fresh
in the ground?

26:52.132 --> 26:53.220
Why does...

26:54.525 --> 26:56.615
the grass never grow here?

26:58.921 --> 27:00.357
Everything rots.

27:00.488 --> 27:02.621
[Alice breathing unsteadily]

27:05.319 --> 27:07.016
They would be six next week.

27:08.365 --> 27:10.324
[chuckles] I know.

27:11.412 --> 27:16.286
Sometimes I worry that they've
drifted from your heart.

27:19.028 --> 27:20.900
Never.

27:21.030 --> 27:26.122
And have I drifted
from your heart?

27:28.559 --> 27:29.648
No.

27:32.389 --> 27:33.652
Of course not.

27:40.571 --> 27:43.139
[Alice sobbing softly]

27:55.499 --> 27:56.805
You should go home, Alice.

27:59.155 --> 28:00.243
Try to get some rest.

28:05.988 --> 28:08.948
[Alice cries]

28:15.345 --> 28:18.000
[pencil scraping]

28:30.056 --> 28:31.274
Thank you for coming.

28:33.363 --> 28:34.843
It means a lot to me,

28:34.974 --> 28:36.279
and my father.

28:36.410 --> 28:37.324
Of course.

28:39.369 --> 28:41.545
Able.

28:41.676 --> 28:43.852
The other night I didn't mean
to embarrass you.

28:46.028 --> 28:47.987
I shouldn't have.

28:48.117 --> 28:50.250
I just thought
you might have liked it.

28:51.468 --> 28:52.556
Me.

28:52.687 --> 28:54.558
I mean, the kiss.

28:54.689 --> 28:55.516
I don't know what
I'm trying to say.

28:55.646 --> 28:56.996
I do.

28:58.301 --> 29:00.303
Like you, I mean.

29:02.392 --> 29:04.438
-Then why didn't you--
-I can't.

29:06.614 --> 29:08.485
Wecan't.

29:10.487 --> 29:12.272
If I was caught
kissing a white girl...

29:14.491 --> 29:15.797
I'd be strung up.

29:17.668 --> 29:20.019
-I'm not white.
-White enough to get me killed.

29:23.631 --> 29:25.938
-What if--
-There are no ifs!

29:26.068 --> 29:27.374
Not for folks like me.

29:34.076 --> 29:35.599
Does Mr. Boone
really believe

29:35.730 --> 29:37.601
his cousin is
inside this house?

29:37.732 --> 29:39.038
You saw the tunnel.

29:41.301 --> 29:42.476
I knew Phillip
and Stephen Boone.

29:43.782 --> 29:45.348
I worked for both of them.

29:46.567 --> 29:48.090
They were normal men.

29:52.138 --> 29:53.313
Until they weren't.

29:55.010 --> 29:56.055
Your father...

29:57.926 --> 30:00.450
there's a weight on him.
I've seen it before.

30:00.581 --> 30:02.278
It's what drove Phillip
and Stephen crazy--

30:02.409 --> 30:04.063
My father isn't mad!

30:06.021 --> 30:07.675
I'm sorry.

30:07.806 --> 30:09.285
I didn't mean
to offend you.

30:14.334 --> 30:22.342
My mother's death
changed everything.

30:22.472 --> 30:23.343
We're all
a little different now.

30:25.301 --> 30:27.216
He's just never grieved.

30:31.177 --> 30:32.831
He's the strongest man I know.

30:36.747 --> 30:37.966
[grunts]

30:39.489 --> 30:40.360
[gasps]

30:50.544 --> 30:51.501
[grunts in disgust]

30:58.552 --> 31:01.294
[breathing unsteadily]

31:08.475 --> 31:10.999
[grunts]

31:11.130 --> 31:15.438
♪♪♪

31:15.569 --> 31:18.180
[moans loudly]

31:27.581 --> 31:29.670
-[creaking]
-[breathing deeply]

31:29.800 --> 31:31.628
[creaking, footsteps]

31:34.370 --> 31:36.329
[rattling]

31:41.160 --> 31:42.030
[gun cocks]

32:06.489 --> 32:07.577
[horse snorts]

32:11.320 --> 32:12.408
Constable?

32:24.899 --> 32:26.945
[indistinct moaning]

32:29.382 --> 32:30.383
[furniture scraping]

32:40.567 --> 32:42.612
[creaking and moaning]

32:47.182 --> 32:48.444
[woman] Ah...!

32:55.277 --> 32:56.365
Mrs. Dennison?

32:58.715 --> 32:59.978
[breathing deeply]

33:03.285 --> 33:04.417
Mrs. Dennison?

33:11.641 --> 33:12.642
[Rebecca screams]

33:16.385 --> 33:19.519
♪♪♪

33:26.265 --> 33:27.005
You there!

33:31.531 --> 33:32.619
It can't be.

33:34.490 --> 33:35.448
[growls]

33:36.884 --> 33:38.016
No!

33:40.670 --> 33:42.672
[Rebecca screams]

33:42.803 --> 33:45.197
What in blazes
are you doing out here?

33:45.327 --> 33:46.502
Phillip Boone!

33:46.633 --> 33:47.938
What?

33:48.069 --> 33:49.636
Phillip Boone!
I just saw him!

33:49.766 --> 33:51.333
He was in your home!

33:51.464 --> 33:52.900
-I followed him here.
-Rebecca, slow down!

33:53.031 --> 33:54.510
He's alive, Mr. Dennison!

33:54.641 --> 33:55.816
We thought it was Stephen
at Chapelwaite,

33:55.946 --> 33:57.296
-but it's not, it's Phillip!
-Stop it! Stop it!

33:57.426 --> 33:59.385
I saw him.

33:59.515 --> 34:00.603
He attacked Mary.

34:02.779 --> 34:05.434
Damn it. Go home!
You go home now.

34:08.916 --> 34:10.483
[breathing deeply]

34:31.808 --> 34:33.636
[floor creaking]

35:00.794 --> 35:02.230
-Mother?
-[door closes]

35:04.102 --> 35:06.539
Rebecca!
What's the matter?

35:06.669 --> 35:08.758
The windows upstairs.
Are any open?

35:08.889 --> 35:10.456
I don't think so.

35:10.586 --> 35:12.284
-[baby fussing]
-We need to check every one,

35:12.414 --> 35:14.460
make sure
they're fastened tight.

35:14.590 --> 35:16.201
And lock every room, too.

35:16.331 --> 35:17.854
Rebecca, stop.

35:17.985 --> 35:19.595
Wha-what do...
Explain yourself.

35:19.726 --> 35:21.336
Phillip Boone is alive.

35:21.467 --> 35:22.729
He attacked Mary Dennison!

35:22.859 --> 35:24.644
-[baby crying]
-[Faith shushes]

35:24.774 --> 35:26.428
Phillip Boone is dead.

35:26.559 --> 35:27.951
No, he is not.

35:28.082 --> 35:29.388
I saw it myself.

35:32.652 --> 35:34.001
How many guests
do you have here?

35:34.132 --> 35:35.916
There's no one here
but Faith and I.

35:36.046 --> 35:38.310
Find Father's gun!
Protect yourselves.

35:38.440 --> 35:40.050
I have to go.

35:40.181 --> 35:42.749
Rebecca, it's Chapelwaite.
It's got you out of sorts.

35:42.879 --> 35:44.490
Stay here, for heaven's sake!

35:44.620 --> 35:46.405
I need to get back to warn
Charles and the children.

35:46.535 --> 35:49.408
If Philip Boone appears,
shoot him.

35:50.800 --> 35:52.193
And lock the doors behind me!

35:53.934 --> 35:55.414
[door closes]

36:10.690 --> 36:12.344
[Tane]
Do you think Father's okay?

36:12.474 --> 36:13.606
[Loa] I don't.

36:13.736 --> 36:15.825
Of course he is.

36:15.956 --> 36:18.785
He tried to kill me
last night.

36:18.915 --> 36:21.483
-That's not true.
-[Loa] He's sick.

36:26.445 --> 36:27.446
Loa!

36:28.795 --> 36:29.709
Is Father really sick?

36:29.839 --> 36:31.363
No.

36:31.493 --> 36:33.713
[creaking]

36:35.889 --> 36:37.978
Someone's on the stairs.

36:38.108 --> 36:40.676
[creaking]

36:40.807 --> 36:42.809
-[whispering] Tane. Stay back.
-Come here.

36:44.941 --> 36:46.378
[gun cocks]

37:25.852 --> 37:33.381
♪♪♪

38:12.159 --> 38:13.943
[man]
You remind me of my daughter.

38:19.601 --> 38:21.081
[chuckles softly]

38:21.211 --> 38:24.084
Who are you?

38:24.214 --> 38:26.434
I'm Stephen.

38:26.565 --> 38:27.609
Your father's cousin.

38:30.264 --> 38:32.527
The one who invited you
here, Loa.

38:32.658 --> 38:35.313
How--how do you know
my name?

38:36.792 --> 38:38.751
I know many things.

38:40.230 --> 38:42.320
I know that
you're not happy here.

38:44.670 --> 38:46.324
I know that you're sad.

38:47.629 --> 38:48.935
And angry.

38:52.112 --> 38:55.724
You must feel very alone,
don't you?

38:58.684 --> 39:00.729
I know loneliness, too.

39:00.860 --> 39:02.862
My father
is looking for you.

39:04.951 --> 39:05.952
Is he?

39:06.082 --> 39:08.563
[Loa] He has a gun.

39:08.694 --> 39:11.087
I worry about his health.

39:11.218 --> 39:13.612
He seems troubled.

39:13.742 --> 39:16.136
Unwell.

39:16.266 --> 39:18.791
But you know that already,
don't you?

39:24.100 --> 39:26.015
[Loa, muffled] What's it's like,
where you are?

39:26.146 --> 39:27.930
[Stephen, muffled]
I'm right here, Loa.

39:28.061 --> 39:29.628
[Loa] No, you're not.

39:29.758 --> 39:32.674
You're between here
and there.

39:32.805 --> 39:35.373
[Stephen replies,
muffled and indistinct]

39:42.205 --> 39:46.993
Come, let's speak of
happier things. Tell me...

39:47.123 --> 39:48.516
How do you like
your necklace?

39:51.301 --> 39:53.434
One could hardly tell
it was broken.

39:55.001 --> 39:58.918
That... was you?

39:59.048 --> 40:01.660
Such a beautiful gift.

40:01.790 --> 40:04.532
Your mother has fine taste.

40:04.663 --> 40:06.229
"Had."

40:06.360 --> 40:08.231
"Has," child.

40:08.362 --> 40:11.060
You knew my mother?

40:11.191 --> 40:13.585
I knowyour mother.

40:17.676 --> 40:22.420
[Stephen's voice, muffled]

40:40.220 --> 40:48.837
[Stephen's voice nearby]

40:48.968 --> 40:51.884
[Loa nearby]
No! No, that's not true!

40:52.014 --> 40:53.668
I don't believe it!

40:53.799 --> 40:55.322
My mother is dead!

40:55.453 --> 40:57.585
No one's ever really dead.

41:00.458 --> 41:02.024
Not if they don't want to be.

41:02.155 --> 41:03.765
Would you like to see her?

41:03.896 --> 41:07.987
♪♪♪

41:08.117 --> 41:10.206
-[gun cocks]
-You stay away from her!

41:10.337 --> 41:11.904
-[hisses]
-Don't hurt him, Father!

41:12.034 --> 41:13.601
[Charles] No!

41:13.732 --> 41:15.734
Stephen!

41:15.864 --> 41:16.952
You look at me,
you son of a bitch.

41:17.083 --> 41:22.828
♪♪♪

41:22.958 --> 41:25.874
Find the book, cousin.

41:28.398 --> 41:29.922
What is wrong with you?

41:30.052 --> 41:32.881
You can still save
your children.

41:33.012 --> 41:35.754
You wanted me here.
Well, I'm here.

41:35.884 --> 41:37.582
But you leave
my family out of this.

41:37.712 --> 41:39.758
I can't do that.

41:41.150 --> 41:42.108
-[gunshot]
-[gasps]

41:44.414 --> 41:45.894
[Loa] No!

41:56.078 --> 42:00.822
-[Able] Mr. Boone...
-[Stephen retches]

42:00.953 --> 42:03.912
[breathing heavily]

42:04.043 --> 42:06.611
My God.

42:06.741 --> 42:13.705
♪♪♪

42:25.891 --> 42:27.675
Was someone here tonight?

42:27.806 --> 42:30.330
[soft moan]

42:30.460 --> 42:33.028
Was there a man in the room?

42:35.117 --> 42:37.206
I felt his love.

42:39.078 --> 42:41.297
I didn't want to come back.

42:43.561 --> 42:46.128
Didn't want
to leave the light.

42:46.259 --> 42:48.130
What light, Mary?

42:49.305 --> 42:50.872
Whose love?

42:52.134 --> 42:55.007
[gasps] God's.

42:55.137 --> 42:58.227
[breathing deeply]

43:10.979 --> 43:12.372
Here.

43:12.502 --> 43:17.725
[moaning]

43:37.266 --> 43:40.313
[whip-poor-wills calling out]

43:40.443 --> 43:42.750
Phillip and Stephen.

43:44.970 --> 43:46.319
Both are alive.

43:46.449 --> 43:48.277
How is this possible?

43:48.408 --> 43:50.323
I don't know.

43:50.453 --> 43:52.194
What if he comes back?

43:52.325 --> 43:55.415
Tonight we stick together.

43:55.545 --> 43:57.156
No one sleeps alone.

44:00.507 --> 44:01.943
Are you all right?

44:10.648 --> 44:12.345
Tell me what he said to you.

44:18.177 --> 44:19.918
What did he say to you, Loa?

44:23.225 --> 44:25.271
What did he want?!

44:25.401 --> 44:28.274
Speak to me!

44:28.404 --> 44:29.667
[woman, from afar]
Charles!

44:30.929 --> 44:32.365
Charles Boone!

44:34.410 --> 44:37.065
[whip-poor-wills calling out]

44:48.990 --> 44:50.078
[Charles] Who are you?

44:52.428 --> 44:53.734
What do you want?

45:00.436 --> 45:02.874
[gun cocks]

45:03.004 --> 45:04.397
Not another step.

45:04.527 --> 45:07.008
He talks a lot about you.

45:07.139 --> 45:08.923
Who are you?

45:09.054 --> 45:12.579
We're the Promised.

45:12.710 --> 45:14.755
This must all be
so confusing for you.

45:17.323 --> 45:19.107
Jakub has the answers.

45:20.500 --> 45:22.154
What answers?

45:22.284 --> 45:26.027
To that madness you feel
growing inside of you...

45:26.158 --> 45:29.248
...and in all
their pretty little bones.

45:29.378 --> 45:32.164
Who is this Jakub?

45:32.294 --> 45:34.383
Jakub is forever.

45:36.211 --> 45:37.517
He wants to see you.

45:37.647 --> 45:39.388
Tomorrow.

45:39.519 --> 45:41.042
In Jerusalem's Lot.

45:43.479 --> 45:45.481
Don't dally, Captain.

45:47.353 --> 45:48.615
Lives are at stake.

45:48.746 --> 45:51.444
[whip-poor-wills calling out]

45:58.146 --> 46:00.148
-The worm doth corrupt.
-No!

46:01.323 --> 46:04.936
[all scream]

46:05.066 --> 46:05.850
[body thuds]

46:05.980 --> 46:09.331
♪♪♪

46:09.462 --> 46:12.073
[grunting]

46:12.204 --> 46:20.125
♪♪♪

46:20.255 --> 46:22.257
You have a pretty family.

46:22.388 --> 46:27.567
♪♪♪

46:27.697 --> 46:36.576
♪♪♪

46:36.706 --> 46:42.887
♪♪♪

46:43.017 --> 46:47.326
♪♪♪
